    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Oligopeptide-1 sr-Sea Raven Polypeptide-1 is a single chain recombinant protein produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sh-Oligopeptide-1 and sr-Sea Raven Polypeptide-1. The fusion protein contains 182 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
